title: Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Press Secretary


For Immediate Release
May 18, 2016

 



Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate





	NOMINATIONS SENT TO THE SENATE:

	Carole Schwartz Rendon, of Ohio, to be United States Attorney for the Northern District of Ohio for the term of four years, vice Steven M. Dettelbach, resigned.

	Frances Marie Tydingco-Gatewood, of Guam, to be Judge for the District Court of Guam for the term of ten years.Â  (Reappointment)
